This paper deals with aspect-based sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as double embeddings and attention mechanism, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with optimizing model performance, which is a common theme in neural networks (cs.NE).
